/*
 * This program produces the sense distribution for a given corpus based on algorithm in:
 * 	D. Yarowsky, "Unsupervised Word Sense Disambiguation Rivaling Supervised Methods", 1995.
 * Prerequisites: nltk for Python. 
 * Platform: Linux/Unix
 * How to use:
 *	
 *	1) Prepare a file containing instances (e.g. tweets) with ambiguous word, one line per instance. The name of the file MUST be the same as the word to be disambiguated (e.g. bank).
 *	2) python sense_dist.py word_to_be_disambiguated
 *
 * Author: Dihong Gong
 * Date:  Feb 2, 2015
 */
